<TITLE> 6 get life for murder, rape </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 14 (bdnews24.com)  A Bogra court and a Natore court on Wednesday sentenced six people to life term imprisonment in two cases  one for murder and the other for rape. Nitai Chandra Saha of Bogra district and sessions judge's court-3 gave five people life term in jail in the murder case. The convicts are 'Sumon', 24, 'Jitu', 24, 'Adam', 23, 'Anwarul', 26, and Gittu Manun, 28, of Fulbari area in the town. The court also fined them Tk 20,000 each, in default, to suffer another two years' rigorous imprisonment (RI). The court acquitted nine others as allegations against them could not be proved. Those acquitted are 'Masud', 23, 'Imam', 26, 'Jewel', 24, 'Awal', 26, Mohammad Ali, 21, 'Shakil', 23, 'Jellal', 22, 'Bulbul', 24, and 'Helal', 21. According to case details, the criminals stabbed Rabiul Islam, 22, son of Mafizuddin of Fulbari area, with sharp knives on September 28 in 2006, just the previous night of Eid-ul-Fitr, when Rabiul was on way to home after shopping. Critically injured, he was admitted to Mohammad Ali Hospital in Bogra where he died the next day. Rabiul's elder brother filed a case with the Bogra Sadar Police Station in this connection. Bogra Sadar Police Station's sub-inspector Abdul Wadud submitted the charge-sheet in the case on May 3, 2007 after investigation. In Natore, judge ASM Zahurul Islam of the Tribunal for Prevention of Repression against Women and Children sentenced a 14-year-old boy, Harun, to life term imprisonment on charge of violating a fifth grade student. According to case details, Harun, son of Abdul Hossain of Hizli village under Bagatipara Upazila, tied the legs and hands of the victim and violated her at her house on November 1 in 2004. She filed a case with the tribunal. bdnews2
